[[Category:Pages to sort]] [[Category:qq]][[de:May 11 (Lunisolar)]][[Category:qq]] [[Category:qq]]{{DEFAULTSORT:May 11 (Lunisolar)}}[[Category:qq]] [[cdo:5 nguŏk 11 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[Category:Pages to sort]] [[Category:qq]][[de:May 11 (Lunisolar)]][[Category:qq]] [[Category:qq]]{{DEFAULTSORT:May 11 (Lunisolar)}}[[Category:qq]] [[zh-min-nan:5 goe̍h 11 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[Category:Pages to sort]] [[Category:qq]][[de:May 11 (Lunisolar)]][[Category:qq]] [[Category:qq]]{{DEFAULTSORT:May 11 (Lunisolar)}}[[Category:qq]] [[zh-yue:五月十一]] {{Lunisolar May}} '''May 11''' is the 11th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Wadō|ja|和銅|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|de|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|zh|Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|708|de|708|ja|708|zh|708|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 3|de|June 3|ja|June 3|zh|June 3|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Japan’s first domestically produced coin, the silver coin {{ill|Wadō Kaikin|de|和同開珎|ja|和同開珎|zh|和同開珎|12=draft|12=draft}}, was minted; later in August, a practical copper currency was issued. * {{ill|Tenpyō|de|Tenpyō|ja|天平|zh|Tenpyō|12=draft|12=draft}} 17th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|de|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|zh|Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|745|de|745|ja|745|zh|745|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 15|de|June 15|ja|June 15|zh|June 15|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Emperor {{ill|Shōmu|de|Emperor Shōmu|ja|聖武天皇|zh|Emperor Shōmu|12=draft|12=draft}} restored the capital to {{ill|Heijō-kyō|de|Heijō-kyō|ja|平城京|zh|Heijō-kyō|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Juei|de|Juei|ja|寿永|zh|Juei|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|de|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|zh|Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1183|de|1183|ja|1183|zh|1183|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 2|de|June 2|ja|June 2|zh|June 2|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Battle of Tsurinawa Mountain ({{ill|Tsurinawa no Tatakai|ja|倶利伽羅峠の戦い|12=draft|12=draft}}) took place, with {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshinaka|de|Minamoto no Yoshinaka|ja|源義仲|zh|Minamoto no Yoshinaka|12=draft|12=draft}} defeating {{ill|Taira no Yoshiakira|de|Taira no Yoshiakira|ja|平維盛|zh|平維盛|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Bun'ei|de|Bun'ei|ja|文永|zh|Bun'ei|12=draft|12=draft}} 11th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|de|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|zh|Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1274|de|1274|ja|1274|zh|1274|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 16|de|June 16|ja|June 16|zh|June 16|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Exiled monk {{ill|Nichiren|de|Nichiren|ja|日蓮|zh|Nichiren|12=draft|12=draft}} was pardoned by the bakufu and left Kamakura for 【Minobu-san|身延山】. * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|de|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|zh|Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1576|de|1576|ja|1576|zh|1576|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 7|de|June 7|ja|June 7|zh|June 7|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Tenshu (main tower) of {{ill|Azuchi Castle|de|安土城|ja|安土城|zh|安土城|12=draft|12=draft}} was completed; shortly thereafter, {{ill|Oda Nobunaga|de|Oda Nobunaga|ja|織田信長|zh|Oda Nobunaga|12=draft|12=draft}} relocated from {{ill|Gifu Castle|de|岐阜城|ja|岐阜城|zh|岐阜城|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Births ==
== Deaths == * {{ill|Bunmei|ja|文明|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|de|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|zh|Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1473|de|1473|ja|1473|zh|1473|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 6|de|June 6|ja|June 6|zh|June 6|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hosokawa Katsumoto|de|細川勝元|ja|細川勝元|zh|細川勝元|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander (born {{ill|1430|de|1430|ja|1430|zh|1430|12=draft|12=draft}}). * {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year (leap May) ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|de|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|Gregorian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1865|de|1865|ja|1865|zh|1865|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|July 3|de|July 3|ja|July 3|zh|July 3|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Okada Izō|de|岡田以蔵|ja|岡田以蔵|zh|岡田以蔵|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Sonnō jōi faction activist (born {{ill|1838|de|1838|ja|1838|zh|1838|12=draft|12=draft}}). * {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year (leap May) ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|de|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|Gregorian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1865|de|1865|ja|1865|zh|1865|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|July 3|de|July 3|ja|July 3|zh|July 3|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Takechi Zuizan|de|武市瑞山|ja|武市瑞山|zh|武市瑞山|12=draft|12=draft}}, also known as Takechi Hanpeita, another Sonnō jōi faction activist (born {{ill|1829|de|1829|ja|1829|zh|1829|12=draft|12=draft}}). * {{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治|lt=Meiji|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|de|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|Gregorian calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1869|de|1869|ja|1869|zh|1869|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 20|de|June 20|ja|June 20|zh|June 20|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hijikata Toshizō|de|土方歳三|ja|土方歳三|zh|土方歳三|12=draft|12=draft}}, the vice-commander of the {{ill|Shinsengumi|de|新選組|ja|新選組|zh|新選組|12=draft|12=draft}} (born {{ill|1835|de|1835|ja|1835|zh|1835|12=draft|12=draft}}).
