 monk {{ill|Nichiren|de|Nichiren|ja|日蓮|zh|Nichiren|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} was pardoned by the bakufu and left Kamakura for 【Minobu-san|身延山】. * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|de|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|zh|Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1576|de|1576|ja|1576|zh|1576|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 7|de|June 7|ja|June 7|zh|June 7|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Tenshu (main tower) of {{ill|Azuchi Castle|de|安土城|ja|安土城|zh|安土城|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} was completed; shortly thereafter, {{ill|Oda Nobunaga|de|Oda Nobunaga|ja|織田信長|zh|Oda Nobunaga|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} relocated from {{ill|Gifu Castle|de|岐阜城|ja|岐阜城|zh|岐阜城|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. == Births ==
== Deaths == * {{ill|Bunmei|ja|文明|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|de|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|zh|Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1473|de|1473|ja|1473|zh|1473|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 6|de|June 6|ja|June 6|zh|June 6|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hosokawa Katsumoto|de|細川勝元|ja|細川勝元|zh|細川勝元|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander (born {{ill|1430|de|1430|ja|1430|zh|1430|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}). * {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year (leap May) ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|de|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|Gregorian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1865|de|1865|ja|1865|zh|1865|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|July 3|de|July 3|ja|July 3|zh|July 3|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Okada Izō|de|岡田以蔵|ja|岡田以蔵|zh|岡田以蔵|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Sonnō jōi faction activist (born {{ill|1838|de|1838|ja|1838|zh|1838|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}). * {{ill|Keiō|ja|慶応|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year (leap May) ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|de|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|Gregorian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1865|de|1865|ja|1865|zh|1865|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|July 3|de|July 3|ja|July 3|zh|July 3|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Takechi Zuizan|de|武市瑞山|ja|武市瑞山|zh|武市瑞山|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, also known as Takechi Hanpeita, another Sonnō jōi faction activist (born {{ill|1829|de|1829|ja|1829|zh|1829|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}). * {{ill|Meiji era|ja|明治|lt=Meiji|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|de|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|zh|Gregorian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1869|de|1869|ja|1869|zh|1869|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 20|de|June 20|ja|June 20|zh|June 20|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hijikata Toshizō|de|土方歳三|ja|土方歳三|zh|土方歳三|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the vice-commander of the {{ill|Shinsengumi|de|新選組|ja|新選組|zh|新選組|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (born {{ill|1835|de|1835|ja|1835|zh|1835|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}).
