'''May 11''' is the 11th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senbu|qid=Q96759842|1=senpu}}{{efn|ja|先負|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}{{efn|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}{{efn|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senbu|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Wadō (era)|en|Wadō (era)|qid=Q1373026|lt=Wadō|1=Wadō (era)}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|708|en|708|qid=Q23511|lt=708|1=708}} {{ill|June 3|de|June 3|ja|June 3|zh|June 3|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 3|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – Japan’s first domestically produced coin, the silver coin {{ill|Wadōkaichin|en|Wadōkaichin|qid=Q3565040|lt=Wadō Kaikin|1=Wadōkaichin}}, was minted; later in August, a practical copper currency was issued.
* {{ill|Tenpyō|en|Tenpyō|qid=Q1199879|lt=Tenpyō|1=Tenpyō}} 17th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|745|en|745|qid=Q23612|lt=745|1=745}} {{ill|June 15|de|June 15|ja|June 15|zh|June 15|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 15|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – Emperor {{ill|Emperor Shōmu|en|Emperor Shōmu|qid=Q349263|lt=Shōmu|1=Emperor Shōmu}} restored the capital to {{ill|Heijō-kyō|en|Heijō-kyō|qid=Q862509|lt=Heijō-kyō|1=Heijō-kyō}}.
* {{ill|Juei|en|Juei|qid=Q598057|lt=Juei|1=Juei}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1183|en|1183|qid=Q19723|lt=1183|1=1183}} {{ill|June 2|de|June 2|ja|June 2|zh|June 2|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 2|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – The Battle of Tsurinawa Mountain ({{ill|Battle of Kurikara Pass|en|Battle of Kurikara Pass|qid=Q2889028|lt=Tsurinawa no Tatakai|1=Battle of Kurikara Pass}}) took place, with {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshinaka|en|Minamoto no Yoshinaka|qid=Q1139202|lt=Minamoto no Yoshinaka|1=Minamoto no Yoshinaka}} defeating {{ill|Taira no Koremori|en|Taira no Koremori|qid=Q3055506|lt=Taira no Yoshiakira|1=Taira no Koremori}}.
* {{ill|Bun'ei|en|Bun'ei|qid=Q1010103|lt=Bun'ei|1=Bun'ei}} 11th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1274|en|1274|qid=Q5527|lt=1274|1=1274}} {{ill|June 16|de|June 16|ja|June 16|zh|June 16|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 16|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – Exiled monk {{ill|Nichiren|1=Nichiren|2=ja|3=日蓮|4=ko|5=니치렌|6=de|7=Nichiren|8=es|9=Nichiren|10=fr|11=Nichiren|12=it|13=Nichiren|14=nl|15=Nichiren|16=no|17=Nichiren|lt=Nichiren|qid=Q311478en|Nichiren|1=Nichiren|2=ja|3=日蓮|4=ko|5=니치렌|6=de|7=Nichiren|8=es|9=Nichiren|10=fr|11=Nichiren|12=it|13=Nichiren|14=nl|15=Nichiren|16=no|17=Nichiren|lt=Nichiren|qid=Q311478qid=Q311478|lt=Nichiren}} was pardoned by the bakufu and left Kamakura for 【Minobu-san|身延山】.
* {{ill|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|en|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|qid=Q1145058|lt=Tenshō Era|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)}} 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1576|en|1576|qid=Q6700|lt=1576|1=1576}} {{ill|June 7|de|June 7|ja|June 7|zh|June 7|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 7|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – The Tenshu (main tower) of {{ill|Azuchi Castle|en|Azuchi Castle|qid=Q786888|lt=Azuchi Castle|1=Azuchi Castle}} was completed; shortly thereafter, {{ill|Oda Nobunaga|en|Oda Nobunaga|qid=Q171411|lt=Oda Nobunaga|1=Oda Nobunaga}} relocated from {{ill|Gifu Castle|en|Gifu Castle|qid=Q1367052|lt=Gifu Castle|1=Gifu Castle}}.
== Births ==

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Civilization|en|Civilization|qid=Q8432|lt=Bunmei|1=Civilization}} 5th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1473|en|1473|qid=Q6594|lt=1473|1=1473}} {{ill|June 6|de|June 6|ja|June 6|zh|June 6|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 6|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – {{ill|Hosokawa Katsumoto|en|Hosokawa Katsumoto|qid=Q740354|lt=Hosokawa Katsumoto|1=Hosokawa Katsumoto}}, a military commander (born {{ill|1430|en|1430|qid=Q6342|lt=1430|1=1430}}).
* {{ill|Keiō|en|Keiō|qid=Q776775|lt=Keiō|1=Keiō}} 1st year (leap May) ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1865|en|1865|qid=Q7708|lt=1865|1=1865}} {{ill|July 3|de|July 3|ja|July 3|zh|July 3|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/July 3|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – {{ill|Okada Izō|en|Okada Izō|qid=Q3058220|lt=Okada Izō|1=Okada Izō}}, a Sonnō jōi faction activist (born {{ill|1838|en|1838|qid=Q7612|lt=1838|1=1838}}).
* {{ill|Keiō|en|Keiō|qid=Q776775|lt=Keiō|1=Keiō}} 1st year (leap May) ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1865|en|1865|qid=Q7708|lt=1865|1=1865}} {{ill|July 3|de|July 3|ja|July 3|zh|July 3|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/July 3|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – {{ill|Takechi Hanpeita|en|Takechi Hanpeita|qid=Q1074298|lt=Takechi Zuizan|1=Takechi Hanpeita}}, also known as Takechi Hanpeita, another Sonnō jōi faction activist (born {{ill|1829|en|1829|qid=Q7572|lt=1829|1=1829}}).
* {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|qid=Q3125096|lt=Meiji|1=Meiji era}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1869|en|1869|qid=Q7720|lt=1869|1=1869}} {{ill|June 20|de|June 20|ja|June 20|zh|June 20|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 20|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) – {{ill|Hijikata Toshizō|en|Hijikata Toshizō|qid=Q701182|lt=Hijikata Toshizō|1=Hijikata Toshizō}}, the vice-commander of the {{ill|Shinsengumi|en|Shinsengumi|qid=Q221031|lt=Shinsengumi|1=Shinsengumi}} (born {{ill|1835|en|1835|qid=Q7597|lt=1835|1=1835}}).

